The paper deals with information theory and coding, which falls under the cs.IT sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on multi-terminal communications problems, which could also fall under the cs.SI (signal processing) and cs.MM (multimedia) sub-categories. The paper also mentions lossy distributed source coding, which could fall under the cs.DS (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions arbitrary alphabet sizes and distributions, which could fall under the cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) sub-category.
